# AWS Infrastructure Provisioning using Terraform

## Project Overview
This project demonstrates Infrastructure as Code (IaC) using Terraform to provision AWS resources. The infrastructure includes a custom VPC, Security Group, and an EC2 instance deployed automatically using Terraform.

## Architecture

Terraform (HCL)
        ↓
AWS VPC
        ↓
Security Group
        ↓
EC2 Instance

## Technologies Used
- Terraform
- AWS EC2
- AWS VPC
- Security Groups
- Git & GitHub
- VS Code

## Project Files

- `provider.tf` – Configures the AWS provider.
- `main.tf` – Defines AWS resources.
- `variables.tf` – Stores input variables.
- `outputs.tf` – Displays output values.
- `terraform.tfvars` – Contains variable values.

## Prerequisites

- AWS Account
- AWS CLI configured
- Terraform installed
- VS Code

## Deployment Steps

```bash
terraform init
terraform validate
terraform plan
terraform apply
```

To destroy the infrastructure:

```bash
terraform destroy
```

